rnings.\n- **PLTR (P/E 153.1)** and **SHOP (P/E 108.2)** remain richly valued despite this week's declines.\n- **QQQ P/E at 34.7** vs. **SPY at 27.7** \u2014 the growth-vs-value spread is widening.\n- **TLT (+1.32%)** and **BND (+0.60%)** rose, suggesting yields softened \u2014 supportive for growth multiples.\n- **IWM P/E at 19.6** remains the cheapest broad index by valuation.\n\n## 5. Themes to Watch\n- **Semiconductor momentum:** AMD's +33% move and NVDA's volume spike suggest a chip-cycle catalyst (earnings, AI capex guidance, or M&A) \u2014 monitor for follow-through or exhaustion.\n- **Energy breakdown:** XLE -6.2% with XOM/CVX both down ~5-6% points to either crude weakness or sector rotation. Watch oil prices and OPEC headlines.\n- **Precious metals + equities rally:** SLV +10.7% and GLD +4.6% alongside stock gains is atypical \u2014 may signal inflation hedging or dollar weakness.\n- **Crypto divergence:** BTC (-0.66%) and ETH (-0.97%) lagged risk assets, while SOL (+5.22%) and LINK (+5.40%) outperformed \u2014 altcoin rotation underway.\n- **SHOP's -13% drop** warrants a look at e-commerce fundamentals.\n- **Bond rally** alongside equities suggests easing rate expectations \u2014 watch upcoming CPI/Fed commentary.\n\n*Monitor for confirmation or reversal of the tech-led leadership next week.*",
